HEADWORD: Rhabdite
<hw>Rhab"dite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"ra`bdos</grk> a rod.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
minute smooth rodlike or fusiform structure found in the tissues of many
Turbellaria.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the hard parts forming the
ovipositor of insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhabdocoela</ent>⟦br⟧
